## Masonry Gallery (`MasonryGallery.tsx`)

**Pinterest-Style Layout:**

**Key Characteristics:**
- **Columns:** 5 desktop, 3-4 tablet, 2 mobile
- **Variable heights:** Images maintain aspect ratio
- **Tight gaps:** 16-20px between images
- **Lazy loading:** Load images as user scrolls (critical for performance)
- **Hover overlay:** Design name + save button

**Implementation Notes:**
```typescript
// Use CSS columns or library like react-masonry-css
<div className="masonry-grid">
  {images.map(image => (
    <div className="masonry-item">
      <img loading="lazy" ... />
      <div className="overlay">
        <p>{image.title}</p>
        <button>Save</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  ))}
</div>

// CSS
.masonry-grid {
  column-count: 5;
  column-gap: 16px;
}

@media (max-width: 1024px) {
  .masonry-grid { column-count: 3; }
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .masonry-grid { column-count: 2; }
}
```

**Lazy Loading Strategy (Pinterest-style):**
1. Load first 20-30 images visible in viewport
2. As user scrolls down, detect when they're 2-3 rows from bottom
3. Load next batch of 20-30 images
4. Continue infinitely or add "Load More" button
5. Show loading skeleton while images load

**Image Hover Overlay:**
```
┌─────────────┐
│             │
│    Image    │
│             │
│ ┌─────────┐ │ ← On hover
│ │ Title   │ │
│ │ [Save]  │ │
│ └─────────┘ │
└─────────────┘
```

- Semi-transparent dark overlay (rgba(0,0,0,0.6))
- Design name in white text
- "Save" button (optional Pinterest-style save)
- Smooth fade-in (0.3s)

