## Image Loading Performance

**Critical for heavy image pages:**

### Lazy Loading Implementation
```typescript
// Only load images in viewport + next 2-3 rows
const [visibleImages, setVisibleImages] = useState([]);

useEffect(() => {
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => {
      entries.forEach(entry => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          loadImage(entry.target);
        }
      });
    },
    { rootMargin: '400px' } // Load 400px before visible
  );
  
  // Observe image containers
}, []);
```

### Image Optimization
- Serve different sizes: thumbnail (400px), medium (800px), full (1200px)
- WebP format with JPEG fallback
- Compress heavily (quality 75-80%)
- Use Next.js Image component with sizes prop

### Progressive Loading
- Load low-quality placeholder first (blur)
- Fade in full image when loaded
- Smooth transition (0.3s)

